[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Welcome to the Course!"]
[Result "*"]
[PlyCount "1"]
[GameId "2123892846743623"]

1. Z0 ({(Dear chess enthusiasts, welcome to my first Chessable course! I am French Grandmaster Laurent Fressinet, former 2700 player from 2010 till 2015, twice French champion and member of the French national team in 11 Olympiads gold medallist on 4th board in 2016. I also worked for Chess24 and did a lot of live commentary mainly in French; you can find more than 1000 hours of live commentary on YouTube, so I got used to and enjoyed sharing my passion and knowledge with as many people as possible. But if you know me, it is probably because I am a former second of Magnus Carlsen, whom I helped from 2013 to 2023. I was the only second to participate in all his World Championship matches, and I also helped him in most of his classical tournaments and rapid tournaments during that period in very close collaboration with Peter Heine Nielsen. Obviously, the most intense periods were during the WC preparation and the matches. That was tough work, incredibly stressful during the matches, but without a doubt, the most exciting experience in my chess career. To be honest, when I agreed to create this course, I didn’t expect that it would be so different from what I had done before. But it was! I had to explain every nuance, every move order, and basically everything! This course will be useful from the club level players to top GMs. It is actually not about your level but about your style: you have to be ready to get unbalanced and good! positions right from the start of the game. I am used to WC prep, so it is just inconceivable for me to send something I am not happy with. I am very happy with the final product, but it took a lot of time. That resulted in several missed deadlines, and I would like to take the opportunity to thank the entire Chessable team for their serious work and even more for their patience! During the 2018 Candidates, we were in a training camp with Peter and Magnus. The day Fabiano Caruana qualified for the match, Magnus said it would be nice to have winning chances as Black and that he would feel comfortable playing Rossolimo as Black versus Caruana at that time, Caruana was almost exclusively playing 1.e4 and the Rossolimo)} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {(. I was a bit surprised as Magnus is so solid in 1.e4 e5. He actually never lost a game in a WC match with that! But after all, Fabi had a very solid repertoire as Black Petrov and Queen's Gambit Declined are not easy to crack, and it made perfect sense. We were six months away from the match. GM Daniil Dubov a great Sveshnikov expert was included on the team, and some serious prep was done. We stuck to the idea of playing the Sveshnikov playing the Rossolimo implied the Sveshnikov, and in Game 1 of his 2018 match vs Caruana, Magnus outplayed him in a sharp Rossolimo… Unfortunately, he missed several wins in time trouble, but his early conclusion was absolutely correct. He got his best winning chances as Black that first game and Game 12 in an open Sveshnikov. In the rapid tie-breaks, he won Game 2 in an open Sveshnikov. It also served him well in the following years and brought him some nice wins. It was nice to have the Sveshnikov as a weapon. I believe that 1.e4 e5 might suit Magnus’s style even better, but against a strong and well-prepared opponent that’s what you get in top tournaments!, it is very difficult to get winning chances. So I was kind of forced to prepare the Sveshnikov in great detail before the match, during the match, and after the match! and I must admit that I really like the opening: sound and aggressive. Unsurprisingly, it was played on a regular basis by some of the greatest: Kasparov, Kramnik, Caruana himself, MVL… It is simply a great way to play for a win against 1.e4. As you might have guessed, we will follow a lot of Magnus’s lines in this course. But you will get a bunch of novelties. Theory always develops, and I have kept track of recent developments while anticipating possible improvements. Obviously, this course was done with the best engines available Stockfish and Leela and the best database Mega Database and correspondence games. I really hope that you will enjoy this journey into the Sveshnikov as much as I do, and I am looking forward to continuing that journey with your feedback and comments! Laurent)}) *

[Event "Lifetime Repertoires: Fressinet’s Sveshnikov Sicilian"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
