1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 ({The starting position of the Open Sveshnikov. Actually,} 5... e5 {(is a very dynamic move: it creates a threat of winning a piece should be spotted by your opponent!, therefore winning some time for our development as White will have to lose a tempo by moving the knight and, more importantly, Black has a weak square on [d5]. We will have to compensate for that with once again! dynamic play.)}) 6. Ndb5 {That's the move! It is actually quite funny that White has a bunch of options, but none of them are even close to being dangerous options.} (6. Nf5 {is probably the best of the sidelines, but Black is at least fine by precise play after} d5 $1 {.}) 6... d6 {We are threatening to go ...[a6]-...[b5] and embarrass the knights. Here is the first real crossroads.} 7. Bg5 {The main move by far and very logical. White wants to occupy the beautiful [d5]-square without exchanging their knight.} a6 8. Na3 b5 (8... b5 {White has two main options} 9. Bxf6 {and Nd5 . Though 9.Nab1 (has also gained some popularity recently, thanks to a course by Anish Giri on this very website! But we will be well prepared and have a nice solution including a very interesting novelty hey Anish, you have to click on buy if you wanna know!.)}) 9. Bxf6 ({Together with} 9. Nd5 {, this is one of the main Sveshnikov lines.}) 9... gxf6 {Forced, damaging our pawn structure but giving us a possibility to go for dynamic play with the future ...[f5].} 10. Nd5 Bg7 11. g3 $5 ({This is a decent alternative to White's main lines} 11. Bd3 {and 11.c3 , see in the previous variations.}) 11... Ne7 {[%cal Ge7d5] We continue with our usual plan.} 12. Bg2 {This is, of course, possible, but we get what we want after the simple knight trade.} Nxd5 13. Qxd5 Be6 14. Qd3 (14. Qc6+ {does not achieve anything.} Ke7 15. Qb7+ Qd7 16. Qxd7+ Kxd7 {, we get an easy play with the two bishops. ...[Rab8], ...[a5] and ...[Bh6] are in the cards.}) 14... Qd7 $1 {[%cal Yf6f5,Ya8d8] Preparing for our usual ...[f5] plan.} 15. O-O O-O {With a balanced position.} *

