1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 {Here, White has tried all the possible moves with the knight and we will briefly check each of them in this chapter.} 6. Nxc6 {Not very ambitious. This allows us to improve our pawn structure.} bxc6 7. Bg5 {Here, we get to ask White some questions.} Rb8 {[%csl Rb2]} (7... Rb8 {Now,} 8. b3 {looks just bad and White's best try is to protect the pawn.}) 8. Rb1 {Obviously, not the ideal square for the rook.} h6 {Some more questions for White!} 9. Bh4 {The most played, but loses immediately.} Qa5 $19 {[%cal Gb8b2,Gf6e4] White cannot handle all the threats.} 10. Bxf6 Rxb2 11. Rxb2 Qxc3+ 12. Qd2 Qxb2 {[%cal Gf8b4,Gf6g7] And the bishop will need to be abandoned as there are more serious threats than ...[gxf6]. Namely, ...[Bb4], skewering White's queen.} *

