1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Ndb5 d6 7. Bg5 a6 8. Na3 b5 9. Nd5 Be7 10. Bxf6 Bxf6 11. Bd3 {This is similar to the [Be2] line.} O-O 12. O-O Bg5 13. c3 {I suggest to follow the same plan as in the [Be2] line.} Be6 14. Nc2 Ne7 ({We want to exchange the powerful knight.} 14... Rb8 {is actually a transposition to this 11.c3 line which is not dangerous for Black. While 14...Rb8 would be an acceptable move, challenging the knight with 14...Ne7 makes much more sense.}) 15. Nxe7+ {White's attempt to avoid changes in the central pawn structure. However, we are just fine.} Qxe7 16. a4 bxa4 17. Rxa4 a5 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Ge7b7] Followed by ...[Qb7] putting pressure on the [b2]-pawn, which will give us enough counterplay.} *

