lso become a target in some lines.} 13. Bd3 {[%cal Gd3g6] Another way to develop, having [Bxg6] as a possibility. The drawback of this move is that the bishop does not attack the [h5]-pawn, so we could castle easier without worrying about the pawn.} a6 14. Nc3 Be7 $1 {[%csl Rh4] White has several ways to deal with the threat.} 15. Bg5 ({Removing the attacker is a possibility, but after} 15. Bxg6 fxg6 {, Black does not encounter any problems and will be able to castle soon.} 16. Bg5 a5 17. Qb6 Bxg5 18. hxg5 O-O {. The [d6]-pawn is not in danger as we always have ...[Ra6].}) 15... f5 {The principled response.} 16. Bxe7 Kxe7 17. Qb6 Rc8 {[%cal Gb8c7] Followed by ...[Qc7] with equal chances.} *

