lso become a target in some lines.} 13. Bg5 {This looks tempting, trying to prevent Black from developing the bishop, but in fact, we can do it anyway.} Be7 $5 14. Bxe7 Kxe7 {[%csl Ge7,Gd6] The king protects the [d6]-pawn and is quite comfortably placed on [e7] for now.} 15. c5 {The most direct approach, trying to refute Black's play.} Bxb5 {It is important to get rid of this annoying knight.} 16. Qxb5 Rc8 17. cxd6+ Qxd6 {Now, White can grab a pawn, but it's not such a good idea.} 18. Qxb7+ Kf8 {[%cal Ga8b8,Gg6f4] All the black pieces come into play quickly.} *

