lso become a target in some lines.} 13. Be3 $5 {[%cal Gc4c5] Here, White's idea is to push [c5], so we cannot play slowly.} a6 14. Nc3 Be7 $5 {[%csl Gh4] Developing the bishop and keeping an eye on the [h4]-pawn, which might be taken at some point.} 15. Bg5 {Playable but harmless. Having less space, we don't mind exchanging some pieces.} O-O 16. Bxe7 Nxe7 17. Ne4 {We are just in time to protect the pawn.} Nf5 {[%csl Gd6]} 18. Bd3 {Now, I like a thematic push.} b5 {Getting rid of our weak pawn on [b7].} 19. b3 Qd8 {[%cal Gd8h4] As mentioned above, the [h4]-pawn might also become a target in some lines. Here, of course, capturing [d6] is critical.} 20. g3 {This is too weakening.} a5 21. Qd2 Nd4 {[%csl Gd4] Black takes over.} *

