.} f5 $1 {Preventing [Ne4] and preparing ...[Bf6]-...[Kg7].} 16. Rc1 Bf6 17. Bd5 Rc8 ({It is important to have ...Na5 ready.} 17... Kg7 {is too premature as now after} 18. Nb3 {eyeing the [a5] and [c5]-squares, we are in serious trouble; for example, it is too late for} Rc8 {due to} 19. Nc5 Ba8 20. Be6 $1 {with a crushing advantage.}) 18. h4 Kg7 19. Nb3 {We have already seen how to react.} Na5 {Now White has a possibility to go for a forced line.} 20. Re7+ Bxe7 21. Rxc8 Qxc8 22. dxe7 Nxb3 23. axb3 Bxd5 24. Qxd4+ Kh6 $10 {And the game will normally end in a perpetual.} *

