ng ...[Kg7] and preventing any [Ng5] business.} (15... h5 $6 {trying to stop the h-pawn is not a good idea as after} 16. Ng5 Ne5 17. Nd2 {± , White's knight on [g5] becomes too strong, and the pressure on [f7] is very unpleasant.}) (15... Rc8 {is too slow as after} 16. Nbd2 {, we cannot go} f5 {as in the previous line due to} 17. Ng5 {± .}) 16. Nbd2 Bxh4 ({This is way too dangerous for Black. Despite being a thematic move,} 16... Na5 {looks suspicious here. After} 17. Ne5 {, the pressure on [f7] is too strong, and we must give away our bishop.} Bxe5 18. Rxe5 Nc6 19. Rc5 Qxh4 {We are suffering, so it's better to have at least some material for it.} 20. Qf3 {forces a long line with ''only'' moves:} Nd8 21. Bd5 Bxd5 22. Qxd5 Nc6 23. Rxc6 dxc6 24. Qe5 Rg8 25. Nf3 Qd8 26. Ng5 Rg7 27. Ne4 {intending [Nc5] or [Nf6]. This probably holds for Black but has a scary look.}) 17. Re4 Bg5 $7 ({The only move not to lose on the spot, but we are not happy to give away our dark-squared bishop.} 17... Bf6 {seems to be the right way to continue, but in fact, after} 18. Rf4 {, White's attack is crushing. [Ne4] is coming.}) 18. Nxg5 Qxg5 19. Nf3 {White is bringing all their forces into play.} Qc5 $7 20. Qd2 {[%cal Gd2h6]} Kg7 {[%csl Rg7]} ({This might give the illusion that the king is safe, but in fact we are still suffering.} 20... h6 {is another way to prevent [Qh6], but Black is still under strong pressure after} 21. Rf4 {.}) 21. Rc1 Qxd6 22. Nxd4 {[%cal Yd4f5]} Kg8 $7 {The only way to stay in the game, but...} 23. Qe3 $16 {Our position is difficult as we lack coordination.} *

