1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {The Rossolimo is the main weapon nowadays to avoid the Sveshnikov variation.} g6 4. O-O Bg7 5. Re1 {One of the main lines for White.} e5 $1 {We stick to the same ...[e5]-system we have already seen in other chapters after White's 5.c3 or 4.c3-5.Qe2.} 6. a3 {An attempt to go for a rapid [b4] plan, but as White is not well developed yet, it is not causing us any problems.} Nge7 7. b4 {Here we have an interesting idea.} Nd4 $5 8. Nxd4 cxd4 {Getting a strong centre.} 9. c3 O-O {[%cal Gd7d5] And we will follow up with ...[d5] enjoying a pleasant position.} *

