1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {The Rossolimo is the main weapon nowadays to avoid the Sveshnikov variation.} g6 4. O-O {White can, of course, start with this.} Bg7 5. Bxc6 {And then go for this.} dxc6 {Here, compared to the main line 4.Bxc6, White shows his intentions right away by castling short.} 6. d3 Nf6 7. Bf4 {This has never been tried and for a good reason.} Nh5 {[%csl Rf4][%cal Gg7b2] And the best is to come back to [c1].} *

