1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {The Rossolimo is the main weapon nowadays to avoid the Sveshnikov variation.} g6 4. O-O {White can, of course, start with this.} Bg7 5. Bxc6 {And then go for this.} dxc6 {Here, compared to the main line 4.Bxc6, White shows his intentions right away by castling short.} 6. d3 Nf6 7. Nbd2 {White can try to go for the same plan without the inclusion of [h3], but we can play in the same style as well} O-O 8. a4 {White will try to take as much space as possible on the queenside} a5 {It is important to stop White's [a5] and to make sure we are always ready to meet the following knight jump.} 9. Nc4 b5 {A recurring idea.} 10. Nce5 Qc7 {[%cal Gf6h5] We will get rid of this active knight soon by playing ...[Nh5].} *

