ht's place, but we actually have another itinerary planned for our knight depending on White's play.} 13. Rf2 h6 {[%cal Gg6g5] A preparation of a future ...[g5].} 14. Nf3 {[%cal Gd3d4] White can try to open the position in the centre now.} Qc7 15. d4 Rd8 16. Rd2 {Now clearly the best choice is to take on [d4].} cxd4 17. Bxd4 {And now we should go for an ugly-looking move.} f6 {The thing is that our dark-squared bishop is an important defender, and to be able to castle, it is better to have the [h6]-pawn well protected.} 18. Qe2 {This is a bit tricky, as some [Nd5] ideas can be in the air at some point.} Bc8 $1 {[%cal Gf8e6] Finally liberating the [e6]-square for the knight.} *

