 against [Bh6].} 13. bxc5 f5 {Now, we can go for this.} 14. exf5 gxf5 {[%cal Gf5f4]} 15. Rae1 {An interesting attempt leading to a very complicated play.} f4 16. Nxe5 {This is White's idea behind [Re1].} O-O ({Seems safer than} 16... fxe3 {, which is also playable, by the way.}) 17. Nxc6 Qg5 ({The immediate} 17... Qh4 {fails to} 18. Nd5 {+- .}) 18. Ne4 Qh4 {White has different possibilities here.} 19. cxb6 {This could be one of the lines.} fxe3 20. Rxe3 axb6 {[%cal Ge6f4] Leading to some mess.} *

