1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {The Rossolimo is the main weapon nowadays to avoid the Sveshnikov variation.} g6 4. Bxc6 {We can call this the main Rossolimo line against the ...[g6] setup. Basically, White's idea when playing [Bb5] is exactly this: to damage Black's pawn structure by taking on [c6].} dxc6 5. d3 Bg7 6. h3 ({A useful prophylactic move. White is not showing his intentions yet, keeping all the options open, notably with his king, which can castle long later on.} 6. O-O Nf6 {transposes here.}) 6... b6 $5 {A very interesting and rare half-waiting move protecting [c5] in the process. The idea is to wait for White to show his intentions. If White plays [Nc3] right away, then we can play ...[e5] followed by ...[Ne7], and at some point, we will go for [f5] as our [e5]-pawn won't be that vulnerable. If White is going for castle, then we can transpose to the line Magnus Carlsen played in his match vs Caruana in 2018, but White lost the option of castling long. Overall, we are trying to play as Magnus did but avoiding the most dangerous lines.} 7. Nc3 e5 $1 {[%cal Gg8e7] Once the knight has jumped to [c3], we can push ...[e5] without any worries. As mentioned here, with the knight still on [b1], the [a3]-[b4] plan is more effective.} (7... Nf6 {would be met by} 8. Be3 {and we have seen here that there is no time for ...[e5] and ...[b6].}) 8. O-O {White's decision to castle short will allow us to do the same without the risk of getting under attack.} Ne7 9. Be3 h6 {This move is directed against the [Qd2]-[Bh6] idea.} 10. Qd2 {This might seem annoying as it prevents us from castling, but on the other hand, it gives us a perfect moment for our ...[f5] push.} f5 11. exf5 gxf5 {[%cal Gf5f4] Now White needs to think about the ...[f4] threat.} 12. Qe2 {Natural, but gives us the chance to castle.} O-O {[%cal Ge7g6]} 13. Rae1 Ng6 14. Nh2 Kh7 {[%cal Ga7a5,Gf8g8,Ga8a7] With a double-edged position, but Black has a clear initiative on the kingside. We will follow up with ...[Rg8], and then the other rook will join the party via [a7]. White will struggle finding any constructive plan except defending.} *

