1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {The Rossolimo is the main weapon nowadays to avoid the Sveshnikov variation.} g6 4. d3 {This can be played if White wants to avoid any long theoretical battles.} Bg7 5. Nc3 Nd4 $5 {As the knight went to [c3], White lost the possibility of having [c2]-[c3] anytime soon, so we could activate our own knight.} (5... Nd4 {Note that} 6. Nxd4 $2 {is losing on the spot due to} cxd4 7. Ne2 Qa5+ {and the bishop drops.}) 6. a4 {[%cal Ga4a5] Played numerous times by Grandmaster Demchenko. White simply wants to take space and restrict our possibilities on the queenside.} e6 {Preparing to develop our knight.} 7. a5 Ne7 8. Bf4 {[%cal Gf4d6] White would be happy to put this bishop on [d6], but we are in time to prevent this idea by some forced sequence of moves.} a6 9. Ba4 b5 10. axb6 Qxb6 {[%csl Gd6] Now the queen is activated and controlling the [d6]-square.} 11. O-O O-O {[%cal Gd7d5] And we are ready to strike in the centre with ...[d5].} 12. Nxd4 cxd4 13. Ne2 d5 {With a comfortable position.} *

