al Gd7d6,Gc8g4] Our idea is simple: we want to play ...[d6] next and attack the [g4]-pawn.} 17. f3 {A natural reaction to reinforce the [g4]-pawn. Now we have a bunch of interesting moves, but I like the direct approach.} Nxe5 18. Ne4 {White's best try.} Nxd3 19. Qxd3 d5 {We don't have time to play slowly.} 20. Ng5 Qh6 21. Qxd5 {And here everything seems good; for example, a simple move:} Bd7 {[%csl Rh6][%cal Gd7c6] Finishing development and activating the bishop by going to [c6] next. It is true that our queen is out of play for now, but White's kingside is compromised, and we have a bishop pair, so our chances are not inferior.} *

