l Ge6b3,Gb3e6] Neutralizing White's best piece.} 11. O-O Bxb3 12. Qxb3 e6 {Of course, we do not take on [d4] as it would give a tremendous initiative for White. Our development is more important than a pawn!} 13. Rd1 {[%cal Gd4d5] With the idea of getting rid of the [d4]-pawn.} Be7 14. d5 {As a rule, it is a good idea to push the isolani as far as possible before it's too late.} O-O ({We can play this way if we want to avoid the symmetrical pawn structure.} 14... Nxd5 {leads to a drawish position after} 15. Nc3 O-O 16. Nxd5 exd5 17. Qxd5 {.}) 15. dxe6 Qxe6 16. Qxe6 fxe6 17. Nc3 {[%cal Ge7f6]} Bf6 {The position is equal, of course, but the game can continue.} *

