1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 {[%cal Gd2d4,Gc3d4,Rb1c3] This is another move order to get the Alapin Sicilian. White's idea is very simple: to push the [d4]-pawn and take the centre. However, this move has certain drawbacks, as it is taking the natural developing square of the [b1]-knight.} Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4] As we already saw in the 2.c3 lines, since White decided to put a pawn on [c3] and not their knight, which would be protecting the [e4]-pawn, this move makes a lot of sense.} 4. e5 {Of course, the most logical reply taking some space and attacking our knight. However, by pushing this pawn, White gives up the [d5]-square.} Nd5 {Here, White has two options: either developing their bishop and kicking the knight off [d5] or taking the centre with [d4]. Both moves have their advantages and disadvantages, and both of them are equally popular.} 5. d4 ({Lines with} 5. Bc4 {will be covered in the next chapter.}) 5... cxd4 6. cxd4 d6 {We need to challenge White's strong centre and also try to develop our bishop soon.} 7. Bc4 {[%csl Rd5]} dxe5 $5 {An interesting alternative to the most common ...[Nb6].} 8. dxe5 {Getting rid of the isolated pawn is the most popular choice.} Ndb4 {This might look a bit shaky, but in fact, White has no way to get rid of this knight any time soon.} 9. Qxd8+ {By playing this, White wants to put our knight into some passive position.} Nxd8 10. Na3 a6 {[%csl Gb5] This is a good alternative preventing both the unpleasant threats [Bb5] and [Nb5].} 11. Bd2 {[%csl Rb4] White wants to push away the annoying knight, which restricts the movements of their own knight on [a3].} Nbc6 12. Bd5 {[%cal Ga3c4] With the idea of bringing the knight to [c4].} Be6 {[%csl Gd8][%cal Ge6d5] However, it turns out that the knight will have to stay for some more time on [a3].} 13. Be4 {The most logical, and here we have a nice continuation.} f5 {Now the best is to take as, otherwise, we could consolidate with ...[g6] and ...[Bg7].} 14. exf6 exf6 {[%cal Gf8c5,Gc5a3] And we can comfortably finish our development.} 15. Nc2 Bc5 {[%cal Ge8g8] We'll castle next with a balanced position.} *

