1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 {[%cal Gd2d4,Gc3d4,Rb1c3] This is another move order to get the Alapin Sicilian. White's idea is very simple: to push the [d4]-pawn and take the centre. However, this move has certain drawbacks, as it is taking the natural developing square of the [b1]-knight.} Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4] As we already saw in the 2.c3 lines, since White decided to put a pawn on [c3] and not their knight, which would be protecting the [e4]-pawn, this move makes a lot of sense.} 4. e5 {Of course, the most logical reply taking some space and attacking our knight. However, by pushing this pawn, White gives up the [d5]-square.} Nd5 {Here, White has two options: either developing their bishop and kicking the knight off [d5] or taking the centre with [d4]. Both moves have their advantages and disadvantages, and both of them are equally popular.} 5. d4 ({Lines with} 5. Bc4 {will be covered in the next chapter.}) 5... cxd4 6. cxd4 d6 {We need to challenge White's strong centre and also try to develop our bishop soon.} 7. Bc4 {[%csl Rd5]} dxe5 $5 {An interesting alternative to the most common ...[Nb6].} 8. dxe5 {Getting rid of the isolated pawn is the most popular choice.} Ndb4 {This might look a bit shaky, but in fact, White has no way to get rid of this knight any time soon.} 9. O-O {This is another try, and here we can take advantage of one detail.} Qxd1 10. Rxd1 {The rook gets to [d1]. It looks well placed, but this move has one significant drawback.} Nc2 {This is the first move to check, but unfortunately, White gets too much initiative if we take the rook due to their superior development.} 11. Na3 Nxa3 ({The best reaction.} 11... Nxa1 {would be bad as now after} 12. Nb5 {, we cannot deal with the [Nc7] threat.}) 12. bxa3 e6 {[%csl Rc8][%cal Gc4d3,Gd3e4,Ga1b1] White gets a more pleasant position despite their doubled pawns on the a-file. They can continue with either [Rb1] to put pressure on [b7] or [Bd3] directly to go to [e4], and we might face problems in finishing our development.It will be especially difficult for our light-squared bishop. Therefore, my recommendation is its immediate development after the queen trade with 10...[Bg4].} *

