O-O {The computer claims that this position is fine for White, but playing this way does not look human.}) 13... g5 {[%csl Rf4][%cal Gf8g7] The idea behind ...[h6]. Not only attacking the bishop and taking space but obviously giving a square for our own bishop on [g7].} 14. Bg3 Bg7 {[%csl Re5,Rg3,Gg7,Gc6,Gb4,Rd6,Rf6,Gg4] Our pieces have good activity, and the [e5]-pawn will always be a problem for White. The bishop looks extremely passive on [g3]. On the other hand, we have some weakened squares on [d6] and [f6], and the king is in the centre for now, so White will probably try to get some play there. The position remains complicated with three possible results.} *

