1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 {[%cal Gd2d4,Gc3d4,Rb1c3] This is another move order to get the Alapin Sicilian. White's idea is very simple: to push the [d4]-pawn and take the centre. However, this move has certain drawbacks, as it is taking the natural developing square of the [b1]-knight.} Nf6 {[%cal Gf6e4] As we already saw in the 2.c3 lines, since White decided to put a pawn on [c3] and not their knight, which would be protecting the [e4]-pawn, this move makes a lot of sense.} 4. e5 {Of course, the most logical reply taking some space and attacking our knight. However, by pushing this pawn, White gives up the [d5]-square.} Nd5 {Here, White has two options: either developing their bishop and kicking the knight off [d5] or taking the centre with [d4]. Both moves have their advantages and disadvantages, and both of them are equally popular.} 5. d4 ({Lines with} 5. Bc4 {will be covered in the next chapter.}) 5... cxd4 6. cxd4 d6 {We need to challenge White's strong centre and also try to develop our bishop soon.} 7. Bc4 {[%csl Rd5]} dxe5 $5 {An interesting alternative to the most common ...[Nb6].} 8. dxe5 {Getting rid of the isolated pawn is the most popular choice.} Be6 $5 {A good alternative to 8...Ndb4.} 9. Ng5 {This looks tempting but is tactically refuted.} Nc3 {[%cal Gd8d1,Gc3d1,Ge6c4] Surprise! This kind of move is very easy to miss over the board. By moving our knight, we create multiple threats: ...[Qxd1], ...[Nxd1], ...[Bxc4].} 10. Qxd8+ Rxd8 {[%cal Gd8d1] Threatening mate, so White has no time to include [Nxe6].} 11. Nxc3 Bxc4 {[%csl Re1] With a very nice position as now the white monarch is completely stuck in the centre.} 12. b3 Ba6 {[%cal Ga6f1,Re1g1]} 13. e6 {White's best try to complicate the matters.} Nd4 {[%cal Gd4c2] Creating one more threat.} 14. exf7+ Kd7 {This might look like some kind of achievement for White, but the truth is that our pieces are much more active, and our king is much safer than the white one.} 15. Rb1 {To avoid the ...[Nc2] fork.} e5 {[%cal Gf8e7] With a good advantage. Our bishop will go to [e7] next to chase the knight, and the [f7]-pawn will be lost sooner or later.} *

