t want to give away our bishop pair.} 17. d6 {[%cal Gb5c7,Ge2e5] White continues to play aggressively.} O-O {We avoid any possible trouble.} 18. Qxe5 {This is way too greedy as White hasn't finished their development yet, and their pieces are poorly coordinated.} Bc6 {[%cal Gf8e8,Gg6g2]} 19. f3 Re8 20. Qc5 Re2 {[%csl Rg2] This is completely crushing.} 21. Rf2 Re1+ {With the idea of forcing the white king to [f1].} 22. Rf1 Rxf1+ 23. Kxf1 Qd3+ {[%cal Gd3f1,Gd3b5] The point.} 24. Kg1 Qxb5 {Simply winning a piece.} *

