..[O-O-O] and/or ...[Ne5] next.} 10. h3 {An important improvement for White, especially if they want to play with [Re1] next, but not only. By including [h3] [Bh5], White has [g4] at his disposal, and even though this is not necessarily the move they want to play, it can be a good way to deal with the ...[Ne5] threat in some lines. Moreover, as you will soon see, in the main line, White's bishop can land on [e4] now without fearing ...[f5], which is working well with our bishop on [g4], but not on [h5].} Bh5 {[%cal Gc6e5]} 11. Re1 {[%csl Ge5] The most played, and it looks like a good square for the rook as ...[Ne5] is now not working that well.} O-O-O 12. b3 {[%cal Gc1a3] White is not only willing to exchange the [c4]-pawn but also might consider [Ba3] attacking our queen.} Qf6 {[%cal Gh5f3,Gf6f3] Therefore, moving the queen is logical.} 13. Na3 $5 {Suggested by Norwegian GM Christiansen in his course 'High-Pressure Alapin Sicilian' and also quite popular in my database. White attacks the pawn on [c4] while not really caring about taking twice on [f3] and getting an endgame where White will get bet the bishop pair.} Nd5 $1 {I like this one attacking the [c3]-pawn and centralising the knight. Also, we may jump to [f4] at some point...} 14. Bb2 {[%cal Gb2c3] Defending the [c3]-pawn is way too slow.} g5 {[%cal Gg5g4,Gh8g8,Gd5f4] Here we go for the king. White's minor pieces are far from the king, and we get a nice attack by playing natural moves.} 15. Nxc4 Rg8 $1 {[%csl Rg1][%cal Gg5g4,Gd5f4] Here we go for the king. Honestly, I would be panicking as White; they are just a pawn up, and Black has a tremendous attack.} 16. Be4 {[%cal Ge4f3]} g4 17. Nh2 $1 {The only way to slow down a bit the attack on the g-line, but Black is winning material.} g3 $1 {[%cal Gh5d1,Gg3f2]} 18. Qxh5 gxf2+ 19. Kh1 fxe1=Q+ 20. Rxe1 {The tactical sequence is over. We are an exchange up, but White has a pawn as compensation. We should be precise to keep an edge.} Nf4 $1 {[%cal Gf4d3,Gf4h5] Nice one! We will invade [d3].} 21. Qf3 Nd3 {[%csl Gd3] Black is better thanks to our blockade on [d3].} *

