e queen, blocking the e-pawn and keeping everything under control.} 24. Rb1 Rhf8 25. a4 Na8 $1 {[%cal Ga8c7,Gc7e6] Our knight has better squares than [b6]. It can go to [c7] and [e6] next.} 26. Re2 Nc7 {White has a few problems here: incomplete development, poor coordination, and lack of a plan, whereas we still have ways to improve our pieces, and the plan of ...[g5]-...[h5]-...[g4] is always possible.} *

