oint. Being a rook up, we can give back some material.} 18. Rxf5 Bxf5 19. Qxf5 Kh8 {[%csl Gh8] Our king feels much better on a dark square.} 20. d6 Rg7 21. Ne4 {We are two exchanges up, but White's pieces are very nicely placed, so we should try to simplify the matters as soon as possible to avoid getting under pressure.} Rd8 (21... Rd8 {The easiest way to equality. After} 22. c3 {, it's time to go for} Rxd6 23. Nxd6 Qxd6 24. Qc8+ {with a perpetual check.}) *

