es, it is a good idea to retreat on this diagonal and offer an exchange of bishops.} 13. Nxe6 ({Taking the bishop is always an option, but here we have a very concrete way how to deal with it.} 13. Bxd4 {is not an independent idea as after} cxd4 14. Nxe6 fxe6 {, it transposes.}) 13... fxe6 {[%cal Gf6g4]} 14. Bxd4 {White's idea, combined with their next move.} cxd4 15. Ne2 {[%cal Ge2d4] Posing the question of how we will protect our pawn.} Kh8 $1 {Removing our king from the unpleasant diagonal is strong. The question is what happens if White goes through with their threat.} 16. Nxd4 {It turns out that taking this pawn is dubious.} d5 $1 17. Bb5 (17. exd5 {is just losing a piece after} Bc5 18. c3 e5 {-+ .}) 17... Qc7 $15 {[%cal Gf6g4,Ge7c5,Gc7b6] With a powerful initiative. There are too many threats for White to parry.} *

