1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 {White still has numerous ways to avoid the main lines. Nothing to worry about if you read this chapter and know the antidotes!} 3. b4 {The Delayed Wing Gambit. Maybe I just invented an opening name, but you got the idea! Honestly, my first impression was not to be very impressed with that move, but it is not as dumb as it looks.} cxb4 {Such early and unexpected gifts have to be taken!} 4. d4 (4. a3 e5 {actually transposes into this line covered via 2.b4.}) 4... d5 {Most straightforward and asking concrete questions to White.} 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. Be2 Nf6 7. c4 {Much less dangerous now than on move 6, a line we'll see here.} bxc3 8. Nxc3 Qa5 {[%cal Ga5e1]} 9. Bd2 Qd8 {Home sweet home! Now we just have a pretty standard IQP position, but White is missing the b-pawn.} 10. O-O e6 11. Bb5 {Trying to get back the pawn, but that's not going to be easy.} Be7 12. Bxc6+ bxc6 13. Ne5 Bd7 {White has some rather vague compensation. Black is obviously better, thanks to the extra pawn.} *

