1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 {White still has numerous ways to avoid the main lines. Nothing to worry about if you read this chapter and know the antidotes!} 3. b4 {The Delayed Wing Gambit. Maybe I just invented an opening name, but you got the idea! Honestly, my first impression was not to be very impressed with that move, but it is not as dumb as it looks.} cxb4 {Such early and unexpected gifts have to be taken!} 4. d4 (4. a3 e5 {actually transposes into this line covered via 2.b4.}) 4... d5 {Most straightforward and asking concrete questions to White.} 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. c4 $1 {White has to be active and create threats; otherwise, it is just a clear pawn up for Black.} bxc3 7. Nxc3 Qa5 {[%cal Ga5e1]} 8. d5 {This looks very tempting, but Black has a very nice and important resource!} e6 $1 {[%cal Gf8b4] Ignoring the knight.} 9. dxc6 Bb4 {[%cal Gb4c3] Black is getting back the piece and gets a much better position.} *

