1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. Bb5 {[%cal Gb5c6] Looks like a missed attempt to play the Rossolimo which is the most serious line in the non-open Sicilians, but it is actually a decent line that was played by none others than Carlsen, Caruana or Grischuk. White just wants to take on [c6] and play a closed position where the knight will be superior to the bishop.} Nd4 $1 {Of course, that's the main problem of not having played [Nf3]. The [d4]-square is now available and unchallenged.} 4. Nf3 a6 (4... Nxb5 {is the most played, but again, it just speeds up White's development and gives them some initiative. I much prefer 4...a6 , which doesn't give White what they want.}) 5. Bd3 {[%cal Gf3d4] By far, the main move. 6.Be2 is a very unambitious way to deal with the line. The bishop is retreating to a passive square and also taking away the square from the [c3]-knight in case White wants to take on [d4]. After 6...e6 (, followed by ...[Ne7]-[c6], Black is at least! completely fine.)} g6 {Now that the light-squared bishop is no longer on the [a2]-[g8] diagonal, we don't need to block it anymore with ...[e7]-[e6]. Therefore, developing the bishop via [g7] is a more ambitious way to play.} 6. O-O Bg7 (6... Bg7 {Now,} 7. Nxd4 cxd4 8. Ne2 d5 {transposes here.}) 7. Re1 Nf6 $1 (7... e6 8. e5 $1 {feels tricky for Black as the dark squares around the black king are weakened. [Ne4]-[d6] is the obvious threat.} Qc7 9. b3 Ne7 10. Bb2 Nec6 {.}) 8. e5 {The obvious approach, trying to punish Black at once.} Nh5 {[%csl Gf4] The knight on [h5] looks weird, but it is actually good as the [f4]-square is available. The [c1]-bishop is not close to controlling the [f4]-square as the bishop on [d3] is creating congestion in White's camp.} 9. Ne4 {[%cal Ge4c5] An obvious novelty eyeing the [c5]-pawn.} O-O $1 10. Nxc5 Nxf3+ 11. Qxf3 Qc7 $1 {[%cal Gc7c5,Gc7e5] Now White has a nice tactical shot.} 12. Nxa6 $1 Rxa6 13. Bxa6 bxa6 {This is a complete mess, but Black is definitely not worse.} 14. d4 Bh8 {[%cal Gh5g7] Making sure the knight will get back into the game via [g7]. A sharp struggle is ahead with chances for both sides: that's one of the reasons to play the Sicilian!} *

