1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 {The Grand Prix attack! Once again, this system is much more dangerous against Najdorf players as they are kind of forced to play 2...d6 if they don't want to end up in another Sicilian than the Najdorf, and therefore can't go ...[d5] in one go.} g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 (4... Bg7 {Note that now} 5. g3 {is actually just transposing to the Closed Sicilian chapter after} e6 6. Bg2 Nge7 {.}) 5. Bb5 {[%cal Gb5c6]} Nd4 $1 {We don't want to allow White to take on [c6] as it would give them an easy game and some nice prospects on the kingside.} 6. a4 {Trying to keep the bishop on [b5] at all costs, but we don't think it is that well placed....} b6 $1 {[%cal Gc8b7,Ge7e6,Gg8e7]} 7. O-O Bb7 8. d3 e6 {[%cal Gg8e7] We continue our development in a natural and harmonious way, while the bishop on [b5] doesn't really help the white cause and is rather misplaced.} 9. Nxd4 Bxd4+ 10. Kh1 Ne7 {[%csl Rb5][%cal Ga7a6,Gd7d5] Black has a very comfortable position with a very clear plan.} *

