1. e4 c5 2. a3 {[%cal Gb2b4] Generally a blitz weapon at the highest level and has been played by none others than Carlsen, Nepo or Mamedyarov!} g6 {[%cal Gg7a1] Exactly the same concept as against 2.b3. We don't want White to occupy the diagonal [a1]-[h8].} 3. d4 {An attempt to develop quickly the queen and castle long as soon as possible.} cxd4 4. Qxd4 {[%cal Gd4h8]} (4. Nf3 {doesn't make any sense, we've just reached an Accelerated Dragon a tempo up!} Bg7 5. Nxd4 Nc6 {and [a3] is just a wasted tempo in this scenario.}) 4... Nf6 {[%cal Gb8c6]} 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Qd3 {[%cal Gc1d2,Ge1c1]} Bg7 7. Nf3 (7. Bd2 {is also an option, but the knight belongs to [f3] anyway. The move order doesn't make any difference.} d6 8. O-O-O O-O 9. Nf3 {transposes.}) 7... d6 8. Bd2 O-O {[%cal Gc8e6,Ga8c8]} 9. O-O-O Be6 {[%cal Ga8c8,Ga7a6,Gb7b5] Black's counterplay is ready while it will take some time for White to initiate any.} *

