1. e4 c5 2. b4 {The Sicilian Wing Gambit. It's not really dangerous if we know what we are doing.} cxb4 {Accepting the gambits is generally the only way to refute them!} 3. a3 e5 $5 {[%cal Gf8b4] Not a popular move, but I like it and thought that having a pawn on [e5] will suit the Sveshnikov spirit well!} (3... d5 4. exd5 Qxd5 5. Nf3 e5 6. c4 {is the main line and also good for Black.}) 4. Nf3 {[%cal Gd6e5,Gg8f6]} (4. axb4 $6 Bxb4 5. Nf3 Nc6 {looks like an Evans gambit but without the bishop on [c4] for White, which obviously diminishes their attacking potential.} 6. Bb2 d6 {and once again, it is hard to imagine that White will get any kind of compensation for the pawn. If 6.Bb5 Nf6! , we got a Berlin with an extra pawn, and the dark-squared bishop developed. That's obviously a very good deal for Black.}) 4... Nc6 5. Bb2 {[%cal Gb2e5] This makes sense as it immediately attacks the [e5]-pawn.} Qb6 $1 {[%csl Rb2][%cal Gb4a3,Gf8c5] Eyeing the bishop on [b2] and threatening ...[Bc5].} 6. Bd3 {Weird but the most popular move in this position! At least it develops a piece and protects the [e4]-pawn. However, it lacks punch and can't create any problem for Black.} ({After} 6. Bc4 bxa3 7. Bxa3 Bxa3 8. Nxa3 Nf6 {, Black is a healthy pawn up, is hitting [e4], and will soon castle and play ...[d6]. Alternatively, 7.Bc3 Bc5 8.O-O d6 9.Ng5 eventually creates a threat, but it's easy to deal with it. 9...Nh6 and it's unclear how to continue for White.}) (6. axb4 Qxb4 {hitting [b2] and [e4].} 7. Qc1 Qxe4+ 8. Be2 Bb4 9. Ra4 Qf5 10. Nxe5 Nge7 {We're a healthy pawn up. This is better than 9...Bxd2+ 10.Nfxd2 Qxa4 11.Nc3 when White has [Nb5] and [Ba3] next.}) 6... Bc5 {[%cal Gc5f2]} 7. axb4 Qxb4 8. Qc1 d6 {[%cal Gb4b6,Gd6e5]} 9. Nc3 Qb6 {[%cal Gg8e7] The only move but good enough to keep better chances.} 10. Nd5 Qd8 11. Bb5 {[%cal Gd2d4]} Nge7 12. d4 exd4 13. Nxd4 {[%cal Gb2g7]} O-O 14. Nxc6 bxc6 15. Qg5 {[%cal Gg5g7,Gd5f6] This looks scary, but we keep a cool head and transpose into a favourable ending.} Ng6 $1 16. Qxd8 Rxd8 17. Bxc6 Rb8 {[%csl Ga7][%cal Gb8b2,Gg6e5,Gc8e6] Feels easier to play for Black. The outside passer on [a7] guarantees us better chances in the endgame.} *

