4 {wins a piece.}) 12... f5 13. exf6 {Not taking en passant would just be admitting a failure of the plan.} Nxf6 14. Ne5 Bxe4 15. Bxe4 O-O {[%csl Gd7,Gg8][%cal Gf6e4] We had to exchange our light-squared bishop for the strong knight on [e4], but other than that, we are doing very well with the central extra pawn, the pieces out and a safe king.} 16. Bf3 Nc4 {[%cal Gc4e5] Now trying to exchange the other active knight. Black is better!} *

