1. e4 c5 2. c4 {[%csl Rd4] A counterintuitive move, frankly, as it creates a hole on [d4]. Generally, it means that White is heading for a manoeuvring game, but that fails to pose Black any serious questions in the opening phase.} Nc6 (2... Nc6 {Now,} 3. Nf3 {is just transposing here.}) 3. Nc3 g6 {We are just playing the same setup as against the closed Sicilian. Making sure that White never gets to play [d4] and have a favourable Maroczy bind.} 4. g3 Bg7 5. Bg2 a6 {[%cal Gb7b5] Already taking aggressive actions on the queenside asking White if they want to allow the expansion with ...[b5].} 6. Nge2 b5 $1 {A very interesting pawn sac, Black is already grabbing the initiative!} 7. cxb5 (7. d3 {is the most reasonable option for White, but Black is having all the fun on the queenside.} Rb8 8. O-O d6 9. Rb1 {Now} b4 {is a reasonable option according to the engines, but it makes little sense to me as closing the queenside doesn't seem to be in Black's favour. I like 9...e6 controlling the [d5]-square and therefore preparing the ...[b4] push as the white knight would have to go to the unfortunate [a4]-square. 10.Be3 b4 11.Na4 e5! losing a tempo on preventing White's [d4] but makes a lot of sense as the White's knight on [a4] has absolutely no future.The engine strongly recommends 10.a3 , avoiding Black's ...[b4] push on good terms. 10...bxc4 11.dxc4 Nge7 Comparing the activity of the rooks on [b8] and [b1] makes you understand who has won the opening battle!}) 7... axb5 8. Nxb5 Ba6 {This is just a very dangerous position for White.} 9. Nec3 (9. Nbc3 {runs into} Bd3 $1 {threatening ...[Nb4] and making sure White can't develop naturally.}) 9... Bxc3 {Very concrete stuff. Black will develop their initiative on the light squares.} 10. Nxc3 Bd3 {[%cal Gc6b4,Gc6d4]} (10... Nb4 11. Bf1 $1 {The only move.} Bd3 {transposes.}) 11. Bf1 {Forced.} Nb4 12. Bxd3 Nxd3+ 13. Ke2 (13. Kf1 c4 {The pawn is fully compensated by the monster knight on [d3].} 14. b3 f5 $1 {Energetic play is the key when you give up a pawn.} 15. exf5 Qc8 16. Qf3 Ra5 $1 {and the rook lift to [f5] is a nice idea which shows Black potential in this line.}) 13... c4 {[%cal Gc4d3,Gf7f5]} 14. b3 f5 {Opening up the game; the white king feels very uncomfortable on [e2].} 15. bxc4 fxe4 16. Nxe4 d5 $1 {This is basically game over; Black's initiative is way too strong.} *

