1. e4 c5 2. Na3 {A weird developing move which is nevertheless seen at a GM level on a regular basis. White keeps flexibility in the centre, but the knight is misplaced on [a3]! Black won't have any problem if they know what they are doing.} Nc6 3. Bb5 {I am giving two options here. In one of them, there is a repetition which is not very reasonable to avoid. So I guess your choice will very much depend on the level of your opponent and your mood on the game's day!} d5 $5 {Pretty rare and with obvious surprise value!} 4. exd5 ({The most normal and logical.} 4. Qe2 {doesn't look very natural to me.} e6 5. Nf3 a6 6. Bxc6+ bxc6 {and again, White has this [Na3] problem to solve.}) (4. d3 $6 e6 {is simply a very good version of the 3...e6 line. ...[Ne7] and ...[a6] is a simple development plan.}) 4... Qxd5 {[%cal Gd5g2]} 5. Nf3 ({The ambitious move.} 5. Qf3 {offers an early endgame which won't cause Black any headache.} Qxf3 6. Nxf3 Bd7 7. d3 Nf6 8. O-O e6 {Black still has a lot of natural moves to complete his development. White can't really challenge Black's rock-solid position.After a typically pseudo-active move such as 7.Nc4 , White is not threatening anything, and we are free to control the centre with our pawns. 7...f6 We'll play ...[e5] with a grip on the dark central squares.}) 5... a6 $1 6. Be2 ({Even if} 6. Bc4 $6 {wins a tempo on the queen, it's more important that it takes the natural square of the [a3]-knight.} Qd6 {and ...[b5] is coming.}) 6... e5 {If such space-gainer works tactically, we should just do it without hesitation!} 7. Nc4 {[%cal Gc4b6] Trying to punish Black at once.} e4 $1 8. Ne3 Qe6 9. Ng5 Qe5 {[%csl Rg5] White knights are jumping around, but the [g5]-knight doesn't have a stable square.} 10. h4 h6 11. Nc4 Qe7 12. Nh3 Be6 {[%cal Ge8c8,Ge6c4,Gc6e5,Gg7g5,Gc6d4] Black is simply winning! White's lack of coordination is quite obvious, and Black has many positional threats.} 13. Nf4 Bxc4 14. Bxc4 O-O-O {[%csl Re1,Ge4,Rh4][%cal Gg8f6,Gc6e5] Black has definitely more space and the initiative. The [h4]-pawn kind of prevents the white king from being safe on the kingside.} *

