1. e4 c5 2. Na3 {A weird developing move which is nevertheless seen at a GM level on a regular basis. White keeps flexibility in the centre, but the knight is misplaced on [a3]! Black won't have any problem if they know what they are doing.} Nc6 3. Bb5 {I am giving two options here. In one of them, there is a repetition which is not very reasonable to avoid. So I guess your choice will very much depend on the level of your opponent and your mood on the game's day!} e6 {[%csl Ra3][%cal Gd7d5] Much more standard and making a lot of sense to me as we are preparing ...[d5], controlling [c4] and basically cutting the [a3]-knight out of the game.} 4. Nf3 {Transposing into a 3...e6 Rossolimo where [Na3] is not supposed to scare us, to say the least.} Nge7 {[%cal Ga7a6,Ge7c6]} 5. O-O a6 6. Be2 {[%cal Ga3c4]} d5 7. exd5 Nxd5 {[%cal Gf8e7,Gd5f4]} (7... exd5 {is the most desirable option to block the [a3]-knight, but we also have to develop!} 8. d4 $1 {and now} c4 {is failing due to} 9. Re1 {, and it will be very difficult for Black to finish development as the vis à vis on the e-line is very unpleasant. After 8...Nf5 9.dxc5 Bxc5 10.c4! , and it is clear that the knight will be in the game via [c2] or [c4].}) 8. d4 Be7 {The knight is still misplaced on [a3] but close to getting back into the game. Black has a very sane position, but we don't have more than equality which is already not too bad as Black after 8 moves!} 9. c4 Ndb4 {[%cal Gb4c2]} 10. Be3 b6 $1 {[%cal Gb6c5] Trying to make White's life harder by not giving any easy exchanges.} 11. Nc2 $1 {Very precise and a clean equaliser.} Nxc2 12. Qxc2 cxd4 13. Rad1 {[%cal Gd1d8] The pin is very effective. White will get his pawn back and equalise.} Bf6 14. Nxd4 Nxd4 15. Bxd4 Bxd4 16. Qe4 {[%cal Ge4a8,Ge4d4,Gd1d4]} Bb7 $1 (16... Bb7 {A nice and only way to 'give back' the piece transposing into a basically drawn endgame.} 17. Qxb7 O-O {is slightly worse for White, actually, as the dominant bishop on [d4] will be there forever.}) (16... Bb7 17. Qxd4 Qxd4 18. Rxd4 Ke7 {, and I don't see much happening in this endgame.}) *

