1. e4 c5 2. Be2 {[%cal Gf2f4,Gd2d3] This looks very innocent and modest, but many strong GMs have played it, so it should be taken seriously. The idea is generally to continue with [f4] and [d3] and attack on the kingside.} Nc6 3. f4 d5 (3... d5 {Now the main move is} 4. d3 {transposing to this line starting with 2.d3.}) 4. exd5 $6 {This feels dubious as it is unclear why White pushed [f4] at all here.} Qxd5 5. Nf3 g6 {[%cal Gf8g7,Gg8h6,Gg8f6]} 6. Nc3 Qd8 {[%csl Gd4] White has two game plans here : creating threats quickly or playing slowly. Either way, Black is completely fine.} 7. Bb5 ({Some sample lines of the slow approach:} 7. O-O Bg7 8. d3 Nh6 {Black has a nice position with a clear plan while it is unclear what White is doing.} 9. Ne4 b6 {with simple development: ...[O-O], ...[Bb7], ...[Qc7], and the knights hace nice posts on [d4] and [f5].Or 8.Ne4 b6 9.Bb5 Bd7 followed by ...[Nf6].}) (7. Ne4 {is the slow approach.} Qb6 8. d3 Bg7 9. O-O Nf6 10. c3 O-O {White will have a tough time equalizing.}) 7... Bd7 8. Ne4 Qb6 9. Qe2 {[%cal Ge4d6] Very active play by White threatening the [Nd6] check.} Bg7 $1 {[%cal Ge8f8] Falling for the trap!} 10. d3 ({A rather modest move which sets a rather trivial trap. White loses two tempi in the} 10. Nd6+ Kf8 11. Ne4 {operation.} Nf6 $1 {...and will pay it a very high price despite the king on [f8]!} 12. Nxf6 exf6 {White has already no solution. The main point is that castling loses a piece.} 13. O-O c4+ {and the bishop drops.}) 10... Nh6 $1 (10... Qxb5 $4 11. Nd6+ {Game over.}) 11. c3 {[%cal Gc3d4]} (11. O-O O-O {Black has a better structure and a nice outpost on [d4]. We are better.}) 11... f5 {The most straightforward. The obvious option of castling is good as well.} 12. Bxc6 {This first, or the bishop would be hanging on [b5].} Qxc6 13. Neg5 Ng4 {[%cal Gh7h6] Black has a dynamic and good game. The next moves are not forced but show Black's potential.} 14. h3 h6 15. hxg4 hxg5 16. Rxh8+ Bxh8 {[%cal Ge8c8,Gf5g4,Gg5f4] Followed by long castle while White's pawn chain is about to collapse.} *

