1. e4 c5 2. f4 {Showing aggressive intentions right away. This has been played by many GMs. Once again, if we know what we are doing, this line is not dangerous.} d5 $1 {The principled reaction. Counter attacking in the centre immediately!} 3. exd5 (3. d3 Nc6 {transposes here.}) 3... Nf6 $5 {[%cal Gf6d5] The most logical as it is desirable to take back the pawn with the knight, but this involves a pawn sac for which Black will get excellent compensation.} 4. Bb5+ (4. c4 $6 {is simply bad as Black gets wonderful compensation right away.} e6 5. dxe6 Bxe6 {with a quick ...[Nc6] eyeing [d4] and ...[Bd6]. That's a much worse version for White than after 4.Bb5+ as White still have to develop their bishop.}) 4... Bd7 5. Bxd7+ Qxd7 6. c4 {Giving back the pawn gives Black a pleasant game without fighting.} e6 $1 7. dxe6 (7. Qe2 {looks like a clever move but don't think it is a good square for the queen on the long term. At some point White will have to take on [e6] and we will have some ...[Nc6]-...[Nd4] ideas.} Bd6 $1 {hitting [f4].}) (7. Nf3 exd5 8. Ne5 Qc7 {Black has taken back the pawn and has a very healthy position. ...[Nc6] and ...[d4] are in the cards.}) 7... Qxe6+ {[%cal Ge6c4]} 8. Qe2 Qxe2+ {[%csl Rd3,Rd4] Entering an endgame where we will have great compensation as the pawn on [c4] creates permanent weaknesses on [d4] and [d3].} 9. Kxe2 ({After} 9. Nxe2 Nc6 {eyeing [b4].} 10. O-O O-O-O 11. Nbc3 Nb4 {, it will be a headache for White to develop their [Bc1] bishop while we keep developing and reinforcing our position with natural moves.} 12. Rb1 Bd6 {with ...[Re8] coming next. Black's knight will land on [d3].}) 9... Nc6 10. Nf3 Bd6 {[%cal Gd6f4]} 11. d3 O-O-O {[%cal Gh8e8]} 12. Rd1 {[%cal Ge2f1,Gd1d3] Basically, the only move not to end up in a disastrous scenario. The king will hide on [f1] while the rook is out of the box and protecting [d3].} Rhe8+ 13. Kf1 Nb4 {[%cal Gb4c2]} 14. Nc3 Bc7 {[%csl Rd3][%cal Gb4d3,Gd8d3] Every black move is creating a threat and that we just keep going!} 15. Ne1 Ng4 {[%cal Gg4h2,Gg4e3]} 16. a3 {Trying to get rid of the annoying [b4]-knight as the [e1]-knight is protecting the crucial [c2]-square and the [d3]-pawn.} Nxh2+ 17. Kg1 {[%cal Gg1h2,Ga3b4]} Rxe1+ $1 {[%cal Gb4c2] A nice tactical shot getting back the pawn.} 18. Rxe1 Nc2 19. Re7 Nxa1 20. Kxh2 Nb3 $1 {[%cal Gb3c1]} 21. Be3 Rf8 {[%cal Gc7d6]} 22. Nb5 Bb8 {[%csl Rd3,Rf4][%cal Ga7a6,Gb8d6] Black will get rid of the rook on the seventh rank on the next couple of moves and get excellent prospects in the ending with equal number of pawns!} *

