1. e4 c5 2. g3 ({White wants to develop their bishop on g2 as in the Closed Sicilian but without playing} 2. Nc3 {to keep the option to go [c3]-[d4] one day. Sounds clever, but that makes the ...[d5] push available for Black.}) 2... d5 $1 3. exd5 Qxd5 {[%cal Gd5h1]} 4. Nf3 Bg4 (4... Nc6 $5 {is also possible and basically ends up in a quick repetition if both sides are playing the best moves. Guess we are already more ambitious!} 5. d3 Nd4 6. Bg2 Bh3 $1 {Typical but nice tactic.} 7. Bxh3 $1 Nxf3+ 8. Kf1 {looks very promising for Black but [Bg2] is coming, so we don't have anything better than repeating the moves:} Nd2+ 9. Kg1 Nf3+ {.}) 5. Bg2 (5. Be2 $6 {is a painful move to make when you just played [g3] three moves before. Unsurprisingly it is also not very good.} Nc6 6. h3 Bh5 {with very easy development: ...[Nf6] and ..e6.}) 5... Qe6+ $1 6. Kf1 (6. Qe2 Qxe2+ 7. Kxe2 Nc6 {is immediately very good for Black. ...[Nd4] and ...[e5] is a strong follow-up.}) 6... Nc6 {[%cal Gc6d4,Ge8c8]} 7. h3 (7. d3 Bh3 {Black is now preventing White's [h3] and will keep developing with long castle and ...[e5] after moving the queen.}) 7... Bh5 8. d3 Qd7 {[%cal Ge7e6,Gg8f6]} 9. Na3 (9. Nbd2 Rd8 10. Nc4 {transposes.}) 9... Rd8 $5 {We want White to show his intentions before deciding if we go for ...[f6]-...[e5] or ...[e6]-...[Nf6] so we may just play a useful waiting move.} ({I find} 9... e6 10. Nc4 f6 11. Be3 {less convincing for Black but no disaster, obviously.}) 10. Nc4 ({Or} 10. Be3 e6 11. Nc4 Nf6 12. g4 {Getting rid of the unpleasant pin makes a lot of sense for White but it also weakens the dark squares and especially the [f4]-square.} Bg6 13. Nfe5 Nxe5 14. Nxe5 Qc7 15. Nxg6 hxg6 {followed by ...[Be7]. Our knight will jump to [d5] eyeing the weak [f4]-square.}) 10... f6 {[%cal Ge7e5] The point of 9...Rd8. We will just go ...[e5] in one go!} 11. Be3 e5 (11... e5 12. Nfxe5 {is not working yet but you have to be aware of the trick. After} Bxd1 13. Nxd7 Bxc2 14. Nxf8 {, now} Bxd3+ {comes with check!} 15. Kg1 Bxc4 {and the knight is trapped.}) 12. Kg1 {[%cal Gf3e5] Now [Nfxe5] is real as the capture on [d3] at the end of the line won't come with check.} Qc7 {[%cal Gb7b6,Gg8e7,Ge7d5] Black has more space. We will finish our development and get better chances.} *

